  "prompt": "I'm sick of hearing about Trump, can I block these questions on my Quora feed?",
  "response": "If you're tired of seeing questions about Donald Trump on your Quora feed, you can take steps to reduce the visibility of such content. Here's how you can do it:\n\n1. **Mute Specific Topics:**\n   - Find a question related to Donald Trump.\n   - Click on the topic tag (e.g., \"Donald Trump\") associated with the question.\n   - On the topic page, click the \"Following\" button, which should change to \"Muted.\"\n\n2. **Block Keywords:**\n   - Go to your Quora settings by clicking on your profile picture at the top right corner and selecting \"Settings.\"\n   - Navigate to the \"Privacy\" tab.\n   - Scroll down to the \"Blocked Words and Phrases\" section.\n   - Add keywords like \"Trump\" or \"Donald Trump\" to block questions containing these terms.\n\n3. **Hide or Downvote:**\n   - If you come across a question you don't want to see, you can downvote it or hide it. Over time, Quora's algorithm should learn to show you fewer of these types of questions.\n\nBy using these methods, you should see fewer questions related to Donald Trump in your feed. Keep in mind that it might take some time for the changes to fully take effect.",
